ast.name: Google fusion table
ast.comment: A library to read Google Fusion Tables.

body.text: The Google Fusion Table requires an API Key. TouchDevelop will automatically ask and cache your API key.
This table contains the list of Hospital in California. See https://www.google.com/fusiontables/DataSource?dsrcid=185189.
You can find the encrypted table id under File -> About in the Google Fusion web view.
Call the `download table` action to download all the rows from a table. Notice that this action returns 2 arguments.
For each row, display the Hospital name.
Downloads the columns and the rows of the table. The field data is stored in the `values` field of each message. Since this action downloads the entire table, it should be used on small datasets
Executes the provided SQL query on Google fusion tables. Please refer to the documentation on how to build SQL queries.
